The paper deals with the problem of detecting unexpected objects in semantic segmentation, which is a task related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a new method that relies on the resynthesis of the image from the resulting semantic map, which involves the use of deep learning techniques (cs.AI). The paper also compares its method with existing approaches, which involves the evaluation of performance metrics (cs.LG). The proposed method involves the use of neural networks, which is a common technique in the field of neural engineering (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of image resynthesis, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM).
